title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 18 §§ 358-2.9 - Covered programs or services
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 18 §§ 358-2.9 - Covered programs or services

State Regulations

Covered programs or services means one or more of the
following: family assistance, safety net assistance, medical assistance, emergency assistance to aged, blind or disabled persons, emergency assistance
to needy families with children, food stamps, HEAP, and any services funded
through the New York State Department of Family Assistance as defined in
section
358-2.20
of this

Subpart. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 18
§§
358-2.9

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
